The '''Blue and Gray Museum''' in [[Fitzgerald, Georgia]] is located in a historic [[railroad depot]] that has been renovated to showcase the story of Fitzgerald's history and connections with the [[American Civil War]]. At the museum's core is its ''Hall of Honor'', dedicated to the Civil War veterans who established the city.  The museum also honors the town's local heroes, including General [[Raymond Gilbert Davis]], the nation's most highly decorated Marine.<ref name=bagm>{{cite web|title=Blue and Gray Museum|url=http://www.fitzgeraldga.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=33&Itemid=148|publisher=City of Fitzgerald|accessdate=2014-04-17|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419015145/http://www.fitzgeraldga.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=33&Itemid=148|archivedate=2014-04-19|df=}}</ref>  

