'''Lambda Archives of San Diego''' is a collection of [[LGBT]] historical materials in [[San Diego]], [[California]], United States.

{{Infobox Organization
| image = LAmbda_Logo.jpg
| caption = Lambda Archives Logo
| website = http://www.lambdaarchives.org
}}

Jess Jessop incorporated the Lesbian and Gay Archives of San Diego in 1987, starting the collection with materials that he and Doug Moore had gathered. Lambda Archives’ primary focus is Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, and Transgender (LGBT) history and culture in the [[San Diego County]], Tijuana (Baja California, Mexico) Region.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gaylesbiantimes.com/?id=16316 |title=GLT » Lambda Archives – Heroes, Pioneers & Trailblazers |publisher=Gaylesbiantimes.com |date=2010-02-18 |accessdate=2013-12-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207013429/http://www.gaylesbiantimes.com/?id=16316 |archivedate=2013-12-07 |df= }}</ref> Lambda Archives is an all-volunteer, nonprofit 501(c)(3) corporation governed by a volunteer Board of Directors.

President [[Frank Nobiletti]] has brought in a considerable number of student [[volunteering|volunteers]] from [[San Diego State University]].<ref name="gay-sd1">{{cite web|url=http://www.gay-sd.com/communities/news/lambda-archives-to-honor-lgbt-trainblazers-history-makers-at-feb-11-fundraising-gala/ |title= |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2013-12-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805211556/http://www.gay-sd.com/communities/news/lambda-archives-to-honor-lgbt-trainblazers-history-makers-at-feb-11-fundraising-gala/ |archivedate=August 5, 2011 }}</ref> These volunteers assist the archive staff by performing various necessary and ongoing tasks.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}}

In 2007, the archives began holding an annual [[wiktionary:gala|gala]] to build additional support in the community and generating additional donations.

==Gala==
The 2008 Honorees were [[Cleve Jones]] and [[Christine Kehoe]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}}

The 2011 Honorees were Larry Bazza, Jennifer LeSar, Doug Case, Carol Pierce, Judi Schaim, Jeff Wynne, George Murphy, Gloria Johnson, Max Disposti, Stewart Bornhoft, Bill Beck, Sara Beth Brooks (Youth Award) <ref name="gay-sd1"/>

==City hall exhibit==
In 2010 Lambda Archives co-sponsored the first ever LGBT Historical Exhibit in San Diego's City Hall titled "A Celebration of San Diego LGBT History."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sandiego.gov/citycouncil/cd3/pdf/100713.pdf |title= |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gay-sd.com/communities/history/gsd-news-briefs/ |title= |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}{{dead link|date=December 2013}}</ref>

==Board of directors==
